article.headline: Belmont 66, Lipscomb 64 (OT)
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Adam Mark scored 24 points and Lipscomb missed a shot with four seconds left in overtime as Belmont beat Lipscomb 66-64 Tuesday night. The two Nashville teams met for the first time since 1996 before a crowd of 4,176. Lipscomb (5-13, 2-8 Atlantic Sun) led the entire game before Belmont (12-5, 7-3) fought back during the final 10 minutes of regulation, finally tying the game at 56 on a layup by Brian Collins with 33 seconds left. Collins finished with 14 points. In overtime, Belmont led 62-60 with 55 seconds remaining when Steve Drabyn hit two free throws, stretching its lead to four points. Drabyn was 9-of-10 from the charity stripe in the game and had 11 points. Jason Jackson sank two free throws for the Bisons with 19 seconds left in overtime to pull Lipscomb within 64-62, but Drabyn was fouled again and made two more free throws. Albert Hacker, who had 16 points and nine rebounds, scored on a wide open layup with 10 seconds left to make it 66-64. Lipscomb managed to get the ball back with four seconds to play but Jackson missed an inside shot. Lipscomb led 35-26 at halftime and stretched its advantage to 46-33 with 15:17 left in regulation on a basket by Brian Fisk, who had 18 points for the Bisons. The Bruins went on a 13-5 run in the final minutes of the second half to eventually tie the game. Chad Hartman scored 12 points for Lipscomb and Jese Snyder had 10 for Belmont.
